author: Steve Burns
title: Ga. man falls from cruise ship; Coast Guard searching
text:
The U.S. Coast Guard is searching for a 24-year-old Warner Robins man after he went overboard early Monday on a cruise near the Bahamas, the Macon Telegraph reported.
Surveillance video on the Carnival Elation showed Kevin Wellons, who was on a cruise with his wife, “going overboard from the 11th deck,” according to a news release from the coast guard.
Wellons’ wife reported him missing about 8:30 a.m. after the ship docked in Nassau, the newspaper reported.
#BreakingNews Missing from the Carnival Elation cruise ship is Kevin Wellons, 24, from Warner Robins, GA.
— USCGSoutheast (@USCGSoutheast) February 14, 2017 Authorities believe Wellons fell off the ship about six hours before his wife reported him missing, the Telegraph reported.
